INSERT INTO goodreads VALUES(33268384,'iGen: Why Today’s Super-Connected Kids Are Growing Up Less Rebellious, More Tolerant, Less Happy--and Completely Unprepared for Adulthood--and What That Means for the Rest of Us','Jean M. Twenge','Twenge, Jean M.','','="1501151983"','="9781501151989"',4,3.7799999999999998046,'Atria Books','Hardcover',352,2017,2017,'','2019/11/13','I''ve been tutoring college students since 2016 and this book and the data it presents exactly matches up with my experiences with my iGen (and occasionally late millenial) students.<br/><br/>The only reason I can''t give it 5 stars is that it''s often incredibly depressing and she sometimes bends over backward trying to find some silver lining in some of these overwhelmingly negative trends.<br/><br/>Whether it''s the anxiety, depression, addiction to social media and their phones, or their almost complete lack of (and lack of interest in) independence and self-determination, or the fact that none of them read long form content (let alone actual books), there''s a whole lot to make you a bit depressed and pessimistic about the future.');
