INSERT INTO goodreads VALUES(47580988,'Uncrowned (Cradle, #7)','Will Wight','Wight, Will','','=""','=""',3,4.5300000000000002486,'Hidden Gnome Publishing','Kindle Edition',288,2019,2019,'','2019/11/13','I have pretty much the same issues as other reviewers.  I''d give 4 stars for what''s there but I have to dock at least 1 for the problems and what''s missing.<br/><br/>The writing is just as good and the content that is there is fine, though not as gripping as some of the other books, especially Underlord.<br/><br/>My problems are the cliff hanger from the last book is given a chapter at the beginning and no resolution.  The book is titled Uncrowned but ends in the middle of the titular tournament with at least 2, arguably more, separate cliff hanger issues.<br/><br/>Other minor issues that others have mentioned, the training does feel a little slim compared to Blackflame and some of the other books.  I could understand that if it meant we got a full story with a proper conclusion and maybe there was just too much to fit into the book but that''s not what happened.<br/><br/><spoiler><br/>I will say that I disagree those who say Lindon does poorly or always loses in this book are missing the fact that as he said himself, losing to Yerin is the first time he''s lost since Dross when he was actually trying to win and not holding back ... and he was holding back for the start of the fight, wasting madra so maybe he could have won if he''d fought full out from the beginning.  Every other time he''s lost since Dross, he''s specifically not used Dross for training purposes (against all the Akura underlords) or he was fighting to contain not to win (against the blackflame).<br/></spoiler>');
